main event: A UFO was sighted in the southwest countryside near Sheridan, Indiana on January 9, 1966 between 7:15-7:30 pm.
interesting points: The UFO had a central reddish-colored nucleus with outer rings of yellow and was more than a quarter the size of the moon.
The UFO moved rapidly and seemed to disappear and reappear.
The sighting was witnessed by a 66-year-old husband and a 13-year-old child, both from Sheridan, Indiana.
The report includes a sketch depicting the UFO's appearance.
sighted object: a reddish-colored UFO with yellow outer rings
photographs: no, the report includes a sketch but no photographs
